import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,8))
    plt.boxplot(data['life_expect'], by=data['country'], vert=False, showfliers=True, patch_artist=True, boxprops=dict(facecolor='lightblue', color='black'), medianprops=dict(color='black'), flierprops=dict(marker='o', markerfacecolor='red', markersize=5, linestyle='none'))
    plt.xlabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.ylabel('Country')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of life expectancy across different countries?')
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.scatter(data['pop'], data['fertility'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between fertility rate and population?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['life_expect'], color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['life_expect'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the trend of life expectancy over the years?')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='pop', hue='cluster', multiple='stack', kde=False)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different clusters?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Cluster')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('cluster').mean()
    data = data.reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['cluster'], data['life_expect'], color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e', '#2ca02c', '#d62728'])
    plt.axhline(y=data['life_expect'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
